## 5. Git Workflow (MANDATORY)

**Step 1 — always check your current branch:** `git branch --show-current`

**Step 2 — branch rules:**

| Branch | Rule |
| :--- | :--- |
| `{{PRODUCTION_BRANCH}}` | **NEVER commit directly.** Represents production. |
| `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}` | **NEVER commit directly.** Integration branch; all PRs target it. |
| `feature/*`, `hotfix/*` | Working branches. Always branch from `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`. |

```bash
git checkout {{MAIN_BRANCH}} && git pull origin {{MAIN_BRANCH}}
git checkout -b feature/<name>
```

**Step 3 — commit format (Conventional Commits):**

| Type | When to use |
| :--- | :--- |
| `feat:` | New feature |
| `fix:` | Bug fix |
| `docs:` | Documentation only |
| `refactor:` | Code restructuring, no behavior change |
| `chore:` | Maintenance, dependencies, wiring |
| `security:` | Security fix (custom type — makes security history greppable) |

**Step 4 — commit & push after every unit of work.** Never leave finished work
uncommitted or parked in a `git stash` — a stash is for short-lived context
switches only, never a place to park deliverables. Include
`.claude/agent-memory/` updates in the same commit as the code they were
learned from: agent memory is part of the deliverable. A task is **not done**
until its changes are committed and pushed.

> **NEVER force-push unless the user explicitly requests it.**

## 6. The Agent Pipeline (MANDATORY)

> **Analyze first.** Any change beyond a trivial single-line fix goes through
> the agent pipeline. Do not write code, edit files, or open PRs outside it —
> that skips QA, integration checks, and documentation, all of which are
> blocking stages.

The entry point is always `team-lead`, run as the **main session**
(`claude --agent team-lead`) — never spawned via the Task tool, because
sub-agents cannot spawn sub-agents. It reads this file, presents a plan, waits
for explicit approval (Gate 1), then drives the stages, pausing once more for
version approval (Gate 2, skippable via `{{AUTO_VERSION}}: true`).

| Task type | Lane |
| :--- | :--- |
| New feature, module, page, refactor, non-trivial bug fix | Full pipeline (Stage 1 — Plan → Stage 6 — Release) |
| UI/UX design or redesign | Full pipeline + Stage 1.5 — Design |
| Small fix meeting **all** hotfix criteria | Hotfix lane (3 stages) |

Pipeline flow: Stage 1 — Plan → (Stage 1.5 — Design) → Stage 2 — Build →
Stage 3 — Review → Stage 4 — Integrate → Stage 5 — Version & Document →
Stage 6 — Release, with commits at checkpoints A–D. Only the orchestrator
runs `git`/`gh`.

Agent definitions live in `.claude/agents/`. Full protocol: see the pipeline
playbook your team adopted (pipeline v1.1).

